06/01/2005
LEFKOSA, Cyprus -- The government of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus (TRNC) decided on Wednesday (5 January) to open its ports to future trade between Turkey, Cyprus -- including the Greek Cypriot-led south of the island -- and other countries. According to TRNC Health and Social Aid Minister Huseyin Celal, the ports would be open to the transit of goods that Turkish Cypriot authorities do not tax. (NTV - 06/01/05; Anadolu Agency - 05/01/05)
